                <h3>New York, NY<br />
                  August 30, 2018
                </h3>
              <p> PGA Aviation LLC (&quot;PGA&quot;) is pleased to announce that it will be a sponsor of the 4th Annual Aircraft Remarketing &amp; Trading Management Forum, which will be held at The Westin Guangzhou, <strong>September 5th through September 7th</strong>, in Guangzhou, China.  </p>
              <p>This forum is the only international conference in China that focuses on the management of mid-life or end-of-life aircraft assets.  The event will bring together airlines, lessors, MROs and OEMs from China and other countries.  Attendees will explore viable fleet phase-out options, and share lease transfer, used aircraft trading, residual valuation, conversion and end-of-life management practices.  As part of the program agenda, PGA will moderate a panel discussion among senior industry leaders on the subject of Mid-Life Lessors. </p>
              <p>PGA is an aircraft re-marketing firm.  Our core team members have accumulated many years of experience with major commercial airframe  OEMs, leasing companies, airlines, and Wall Street law firms. Collectively, we possess strong backgrounds in the areas of Sales, Marketing, Customer Service, Engineering, Maintenance, Legal, Contracts, and Finance. We maintain a strong network globally, and have established excellent working relationships with airframe OEMs, airlines, leasing companies, aircraft investors and financiers, private equity firms, part-out companies, and a first-tier global aircraft appraisal firm. </p>
